    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Josh Lowe** pacing the offense as our premier starts. **Gunnar Henderson** carries a robust 68.83 score, benefiting significantly from a favorable matchup against Schlittler and a prime leadoff spot that maximizes his counting stat potential. Meanwhile, **Josh Lowe** (68.79) is a high-upside play; despite hitting seventh, he draws a exploitable 4.38 xERA starter in Martin and receives a notable boost from wind-aided conditions. We are also high on **Heliot Ramos** (64.06), whose matchup against V\u00e1squez (4.91 xERA) provides an elite SP skill advantage, making him a high-floor selection for our outfield rotation.\n\nStrategic adjustments for today revolve around exploiting platoon advantages and park factors. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.07) remains a core engine for our production, as his strong xwOBA offsets the slightly negative park impact. We are closely monitoring the bottom of the order, where **Andy Pages** (49.44) draws a marginal start\u2014he is being kept active largely due to the base-stealing potential inherent in the opponent's slow delivery, a critical factor given our aggressive pursuit of the SB category. **Nolan Schanuel** (59.87) sits on the cusp of the strong-start threshold; he is effectively our most reliable depth piece today, edging out the bench options by providing a stable floor in a favorable wind-out environment. \n\nRegarding roster management, the depth chart is currently thinned by the absences of **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jordan Westburg**, and **Jorge Polanco**, all of whom remain sidelined on the IL. With **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** also unavailable due to a team off-day, our bench flexibility is restricted. We are looking for increased contributions from prospects like **Jacob Wilson** and **Nasim Nunez** as we navigate this injury cluster. While veterans like **Marcell Ozuna** and **Josh Jung** provide long-term stability, today's optimizer favored the current daily efficiency scores of **Sam Antonacci** and **Jackson Merrill**, who both benefit from wind-out projections and favorable lineup positioning, ultimately keeping them in the starting rotation over our deep-bench reserves like **Coby Mayo**, **Brady House**, and **Dominic Smith**.",
